post_text:
Student Nutrition Great News!!!

Starting on September 21st, 2020 Food Service will be providing meals free of charge to all children 18 years old and younger and no parent/guardian consent form is needed. All children can participate in the program, regardless of where they live or attend school. Parents/Guardians or students can pick up meals at any of the sites.

We will also be changing the times to 9:00 AM to 10:30 AM.
If you all have any questions please call Food Service Director, Christina Martinez at 575-759-2932. Or please call Jacob Herbster, Transportation Coordinator at 575-756-4672.

We do ask that as soon as you get home, please make sure and put your meals in the fridge.

Thank you all for your time.

Good Morning.
Breakfast and Lunch Meals will be served every day, Monday through Friday for all schools and all registered students, unless there is a scheduled day off on our approved school calendar. All meals are prepared at the middle school cafeteria, and transported to the three designated site locations in Dulce. You may pick up at Dulce Elemetary School front parking lot, Ishkoteen and Wild Horse Hotel lots. If you have any questions, please contact Food Service Director Christina Martinez at 575-759-2932.

Also, computer help issues that were to take place at the high school tomorrow, Tuesday, August 25, has been cancelled. We will inform you when help will be available from the IT department. Thank you for your time and patience. :)

post_text:
Dulce Independent School District would like to inform the community that a member of our staff has tested positive for Covid-19. We have closed the building where this staff member works and it has been fully cleaned and sanitized.

School will continue to be held and teachers will continue to teach remotely. Because of remote learning, this was a secluded event and exposure to other staff members was minimal. Building administration will continue to adhere and enforce all New Mexico Public Health orders, CDC Guidelines and New Mexico Public Education Departments reentry guidelines.

If you have any questions, please call Samantha Archer, Acting Superintendent at 575-759-2917 during normal business hours.

Thank you for your time.

Student Nutrition begins August 17, 2020

Breakfast and lunch are free for all students. On Monday, August 17, 2020, meals will be provided for the students at select designated pick up locations in Dulce from 9:00 to 11:30 a.m. daily. This will be both breakfast and lunch meals.
Bus 1 riders: will pick up at Dulce Elementary School
Bus 2 riders: will pick up at Ishkoteen Building
Bus 3 riders: will pick up at the Wildhorse

If your child does not ride the bus, you may pick up a meal at your nearest location.

The designated areas are also posted at www.dulceschools.com under the quick links section, or at Dulce Schools Facebook page. If you have additional questions, please call Jacob Herbster, transportation coordinator at 575-756-4672.

post_text:
Technology Distribution for all registered DISD students will take place at the Dulce Athletic Complex starting Wednesday, August 12, 2020. Distribution will be from 9:00 am to 2:30 pm Wednesday through Friday.

Families whose last name falls between A-I will come on Wednesday. Families whose last name falls between J-R will come on Thursday and families whose last name falls between S-Z will be Friday.

Masks and social distancing will be required, as well as temperature checks and completion of health questionnaire. Only two people per family will be allowed to enter the DAC and no more than 5 groups of two will be allowed in at a single time.

Please Share. :)

post_text:
Good Morning,

Great news! Human Service Department has issued the first phase of benefit of issuance to all students households on May 18th that are currently on SNAP benefits. The benefits went to approximately 87,500 student households in the amount of $313.40 for March, April, and May.

The phases of P-EBT benefit issuance will be the following:

Phase 1- Issue Benefits to current SNAP EBT student households (May 18th)
Phase 2- Issue Benefits to current Medicaid student households (By end of May)
Phase 3 and 4- Issue benefits via mailed P-EBT card to students that receive free and reduced meals that are NOT on SNAP EBT or Medicaid (Early June)

Please be patient as the benefits are forthcoming and still we encourage families to visit SSO or SFSP sites for breakfast/lunch meals in Dulce.

Have a great day! PLEASE share this message with others.

Why respond to the #2020Census?

Census data helps states and communities get their share of billions of dollars in federal funding. Federal funding is used in programs for schools, libraries, hospitals/clinics, fire and police departments, Pell Grants for College, Unemployment, Small Business Loans and so much more. Respond today at 2020census.gov, if you have received your Census ID.

Thank you!

On Monday, April 6, 2020, meals will be provided for the students at select designated pick up locations in Dulce from 9:15 to 9:45 a.m. daily. This will be both breakfast and lunch meals. Meals will not be delivered door to door as they have been. Bus 1 riders will pick up at Dulce Elementary School, Bus 2 riders will pick up at Ishkoteen Building, and Bus 3 riders will pick up at the Wildhorse.

If your child does not ride the bus, you may pick up a meal at your nearest location. The designated areas are also posted at www.dulceschools.com under the quick links section, or at Dulce Schools Facebook page.

If you have additional questions, please call Jacob Herbster, transportation coordinator at 575-756-4672. Thanks and please share this message.

Good Evening.

Per Governor Michelle Lujan Grisham and New Mexico Public Education Secretary Ryan Stewart, all public schools are to take a proactive measure to limit the potential community spread of COVID-19. Dulce Independent Schools will be closed beginning Monday, March 16th thru Monday, April 6th, 2020. As direction is received from the cabinet secretary tomorrow, district administration will meet to discuss directives and implications regarding public education. Updates will follow.

Thank you for your time.

Tonight there will be a college and trade school application night at Dulce High School for all seniors and their parents. We will also offer assistance to any parent and their student with the Free Application for Financial Aid from the Federal Government FAFSA application. The session will be at the first floor computer lab. We will have a brief presentation in the entrance and commons area and then move to the lab. If you are going to complete the FAFSA application, please bring your 2018 tax return documents because the Federal Government requires previous year tax information.

Also, on Thursday, December 19, 2020, All Dulce High School parents are invited to an informational meeting regarding the 2020 second semester schedule changes. The meeting will take place in the auditorium. Please join us at 5:00 pm. Thank you.

If you have any questions, please contact Mr. Dave Mamich, counselor at Dulce High School. 575-759-2951

Good Morning Parents and Guardians.

Middle and High School schedules are being worked on and should be completed by the end of today. Students should receive their schedules tomorrow, August 8 when they arrive at school. Please be patient as we work on this process. Dulce Elementary students have been placed in their classrooms and the staff will guide you tomorrow on their placement.

Also, Dulce Elementary School has openings for eight pre k students. The Pre K program will begin on August 12 for 4 year old children. This school year, Pre K will be a full day, five days a week from 8 to 3:30 pm, Monday through Thursday's and 8:00 am to 2 pm on Friday's.

Please register your student online at Dulce Schools.schoolmint.net or at the registration link at dulceschools.com. Please stop by the elementary and speak to Michelle or Dallas for further assistance with registration.

Thank you for your time. Please share this message.
text:
Good Morning Parents and Guardians.

Middle and High School schedules are being worked on and should be completed by the end of today. Students should receive their schedules tomorrow, August 8 when they arrive at school. Please be patient as we work on this process. Dulce Elementary students have been placed in their classrooms and the staff will guide you tomorrow on their placement.

Also, Dulce Elementary School has openings for eight pre k students. The Pre K program will begin on August 12 for 4 year old children. This school year, Pre K will be a full day, five days a week from 8 to 3:30 pm, Monday through Thursday's and 8:00 am to 2 pm on Friday's.

Please register your student online at Dulce Schools.schoolmint.net or at the registration link at dulceschools.com. Please stop by the elementary and speak to Michelle or Dallas for further assistance with registration.

Thank you for your time. Please share this message.

Parents & Guardians,

The K5+ Summer School Program will have an Art Quake outdoor art day tomorrow, Wednesday, July 17, 2019 from 12:45 to 3:00 p.m. at Dulce Elementary School.

Students will be experimenting and exploring with art to expand on what they have learned about animals, plants, and fish. Don't miss the opportunity to paint rocks, sand painting, and much more. All volunteers are welcome. Bring an apron to join us.

Also, tomorrow is the last day to purchase lunch tickets for the July 23rd bbq. Please purchase your tickets from the office staff.

Thank you for your time! We hope to see you there!

There will be a security gate installation taking place tomorrow, Friday, February 1st at the Dulce Elementary School main entrance. We are asking that all parents and staff utilize the schools access in the back of the building until complete. Please remember that all main entrance student arrivals and departures are strictly prohibited due to safety issues. The back entrance has been designated for arrivals and departures.

Also, the we invite you to attend our awards assembly on Friday, February 1, 2019. Kindergarten through 5th grades will start at 9:00 a.m. in the elementary gym. Please join us in celebrating our students achievements. Thank you for your time.

post_text: Good Morning. Please be advised that the Dulce Independent Schools was notified about a possible threat this morning, but it was not a direct threat to our schools. We encourage all parents and guardians to leave their children in school. We will not be having an early release. In conjunction with the Jicarilla Apache Nation Police Department, all of our campuses will be patrolled today, Tuesday, December 11 as a precaution. Once again, this wasn't a direct threat to our schools. Thank you for your time.
